Requirements
What will you be bringing to the team?
Minimum 4 years of relevant education (master or equivalent) after the secondary school.
Minimum 9 years of IT professional experience, of which
3 years of experience with SOA Platform Architecture and Development.
Certified Architect (Open Group or equivalent) is strongly recommended;
Experience with Linux, UNIX or AIX Enterprise environment;
Strong understanding of Service Oriented Architectures, with proven experience in designing SOA tiers;
Strong background in systems architecture middleware technologies;
Strong skills in Services Design Best Practices, Service Performance Monitoring, Service Performance Tuning, Service Interface Specifications;
Object Oriented skills using open architecture standards, as well as best practices, design principles and techniques with regard to: BPEL, UML, WSDL, JDBC, SQL, XML/XSL, SOAP, Webservices;
Significant knowledge and experience in designing and developing Enterprise Service Bus/SOA/Integration Tier Architecture (BPEL/Business Process Orchestration, Webservices, J2EE);
Knowledge of SOA Design patterns for building middleware systems ground up using Message Routing, Content Enrichment, Message Filtering,
Message Transformation, Guaranteed delivery, Message sequencing, Batch message processing, error handling and reconciliation mechanisms;
Architecture knowledge about Security, Logging, Auditing, Policy Management and Performance Monitoring and KPI for end-to-end process execution;
Expertise in implementing enterprise architecture standards and methods;
Strong knowledge of Cloud Solutions, containerized platforms.
